      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds good in theory, but \"low overhead\" is a pretty broad term. Most people just want to know the bottom line. If I were to put a large sum towards the South Sudan crisis specifically, what kind of percentage would actually be hitting the ground for field ops vs what's being eaten up by your management and marketing costs?",
